Docs.param: If true, gets the count of the contents crawled. If false, gets all the information about the crawled contents.
Maximum number of rows to be returned. If 0 is specified, all the rows are returned. The number of rows returned will not exceed the number specified by the parameter, if it is not 0.
Specifies the URL pattern for which crawled documents are returned.
If true, the pattern specified in is used as the prefix while matching the URLs of the crawled content. If false, the pattern specified in exactly matches the URLs of the crawled content.
Unique identifier of the content source. If specified, only the crawled contents that are associated with the content source are returned.
If set to DateTime.MinValue, returns information about all of the crawled contents. Otherwise, returns information about contents that were crawled after the specified DateTime.
If set to DateTime.MaxValue, returns information about all of the crawled contents. Otherwise, returns information about contents that were crawled before the specified DateTime.
Docs.summary: Retrieves information about all the contents that were crawled.
